This paper presents a novel value-based method for multi-agent reinforcement learning, which is likely to fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves coordination between multiple agents, which suggests the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also mentions the use of a network to estimate joint action-values, which could fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the evaluation of the method is done on a set of micromanagement tasks, which could suggest the category of robotics (cs.RO).
